OpenGL Practical 2 - FLSANT005
==========================
1. In the terminal, call `make` then `make run`.
2. The controls for the matrix transformations are given below.
3. The camera rotates around the origin, as this was specified in the assignment. Object rotation can be achieved though - check line 378 in glwindow.cpp.
    - In order to inspect the object for lighting consistency , I think it would be easier to make the object rotate.
4. Distance has been accounted for in lighting calculations, so please play around with that.

    TRANSLATIONS    |
    -----------------------------------
    + X translate   |       RIGHT ARROW
    - X translate   |       LEFT ARROW
    + Y translate   |       UP ARROW
    - Y translate   |       DOWN ARROW
    + Z translate   |       BACKSLASH (next to backspace)
    - Z translate   |       BACKSPACE
    -----------------------------------
    SCALING         |
    -----------------------------------
    + Scaling       |       PERIOD (>)
    - Scaling       |       COMMA (<)
    -----------------------------------
   CAMERA ROTATIONS |
    -----------------------------------
    X axis          |       X
    Y axis          |       Y
    Z axis          |       Z
    -----------------------------------               
    COLOUR CHANGES  |
    -----------------------------------
    Object 1        |       1
    -----------------------------------               
    BUMP MAPPING |
    -----------------------------------
    Object 1        |       B
   



